The Federal Trade Commission said iteased a requirement that Allied-Signal Inc's Allied Corpsubsidiary get prior FTC approval before making certainacquisitions in the high-purity acid market.    The FTC said it ended the prior approval requirementbecause Allied no longer has businesses covered by the order.Other restrictions still apply, it said.    The restrcitions stem from a 1983 order by the FTC settlingcharges that Allied's 1981 acquisition of Fisher Scientific Coreduced competition in three high-purity acid markets. Reuter&#3;